## ✨ Features

| Feature | Description |
|:--------|:------------|
| 🔑 **Post‑Quantum & Classical Hybrid** | Kyber‑1024 (FIPS 203 candidate) + X25519. The safest practical key agreement even against quantum adversaries. |
| 🧠 **Quantum Preset** | Classical cost amplifier: Argon2id at 2 GiB memory and SPIP iterations at 16M, raising the bar for quantum cryptanalysis.<sup>*</sup> |
| 📦 **Layered Encryption** | Inner XChaCha20‑Poly1305 secretstream + outer Keccak sponge (or AES‑256‑GCM MAC seal). |
| ⚡ **Streaming O(1) RAM** | Never loads the entire file into memory. Uses fixed‑size 1 MiB buffers for all operations. |
| 🛡️ **Paranoid Mode** | Locks Keccak rounds to 24, enforces extra mixing in SPIP, adds capacity hardening. |
| 🔐 **Per‑File Unique Keys** | JIT key wrapping – a fresh outer key is generated per file, encrypted with the derived key before use. |
| 🔎 **Fault Resistance** | Core Keccak permutation is run three times and results are voted – a single silent hardware error is caught immediately. |
| 🧪 **Built‑in Self‑Tests** | Comprehensive checks at startup (sponge, SPIP, JIT, hybrid KEM, constant‑time utilities). Refuses to run if anything fails. |
| 🧹 **Secure Memory Hygiene** | All sensitive buffers are `mlock`'d, scrubbed, and zeroed; heap is sanitised after each operation. |
| 🎨 **Interactive TUI** | Full‑color menu with progress bars, live encryption speed, and easy settings configuration. |

<small><sup>*</sup>Classical cost amplifier only – not a mathematically proven post‑quantum scheme for the symmetric layers.</small>

