## 🏗️ Architecture

```
      Password + PIN
           │
           ▼
  Argon2id (256 MiB default) → Master Key
           │
           ├──→ Hybrid KEM (Kyber‑1024 + X25519)
           │    or Ephemeral Key / Classic
           │
           ▼
  Derived Outer Key
           │
           ▼
  JIT wrap → File Outer Key (per‑file random)
           │
           ├──→ SIV computation (BLAKE2b over plaintext)
           │
           ▼
  Inner encryption (XChaCha20‑Poly1305 secretstream)
   · Random inner key & nonce written to output
   · Inner nonce bound as AD on first chunk
           │
           ▼
  Outer encryption (streaming Keccak sponge or AES‑GCM seal)
   · Keyed by File Outer Key
   · Final 64‑byte authentication tag
           │
           ▼
  Encrypted file ready
```

Decryption reverses the process, verifying:
1. Outer authentication tag  
2. Inner secretstream MACs  
3. SIV against the recovered plaintext  

All checks are constant‑time – a single mismatch aborts the operation.

