## 📦 Installation

### Prerequisites

- **C17 compiler** (GCC ≥ 8, Clang ≥ 10)
- **libsodium ≥ 1.0.18** (development files)
- **Kyber‑1024 reference implementation** providing `kyber/kem.h` with `KYBER_*` constants and functions.  
  Place it in the `kyber/` subdirectory. (Works with [PQClean](https://github.com/PQClean/PQClean) or [liboqs](https://openquantumsafe.org/).)

#### Install libsodium

```bash
# Debian / Ubuntu
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install libsodium-dev

# macOS (Homebrew)
brew install libsodium
```

### Build Axis‑512

```bash
gcc -std=c17 -O2 -march=native -o axis512 axis.c intern.c \
    -lsodium -lpthread -ldl -lm \
    -I. -Ikyber \
    -D_DEFAULT_SOURCE -D_POSIX_C_SOURCE=200809L
```

Optional security hardening flags:

```bash
gcc ... -fstack-protector-strong -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 -Wl,-z,relro,-z,now
```

(You can also use the provided `Makefile` if available in your repository.)

