## 📁 File Format

The encrypted file is self‑contained and contains (in order):

```
- salt (32 bytes)
- (if Kyber mode) SKE header: encrypted Kyber+X25519 secret keys
- (if Kyber mode) Kyber ciphertext + ephemeral X25519 public key
- (if Ephemeral mode) encrypted ephemeral key
- JIT wrapped file outer key (nonce + wrapped key)
- SIV (64 bytes)
- Outer ciphertext stream (inner header + inner ciphertext + outer authentication tag)
```

All sizes are fixed; no delimiters are needed. The binary layout is endian‑ness independent for the salt and SIV (explicit little‑endian encoding where needed).

